#!CSeaGreen #!N  #!Rspeed Changing 
the Rate of Frame Display: Throttle... #!N #!EC #!N #!N You 
can specify a maximum rate of speed to display new frames. 
This rate is specified as a number of seconds per frame 
(i.e., the minimum number of seconds that any frame will be 
displayed before advancing to the next frame). #!N #!N To change 
the rate of display, do the following: #!N #!I0 #!N  #!F-adobe-times-medium-r-normal--18*   
#!N #!N #!I30 #!N 1. Select the  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   Throttle... #!EF option 
from the  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   Options #!EF pull-down menu in the Image window. 
A dialog box appears, as illustrated in  #!Lthrot63,dxall329 f Figure 63  #!EL  . #!Cbrown #!N 
 #!F-adobe-times-medium-r-normal--18*    #!Rthrot63 #!N Graphics omitted from Online Documentation. Please see the 
manual. #!N #!N Figure 63. Throttle Dialog Box #!EF #!N #!EC 
#!N #!I30 #!N 2. Edit the  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   Seconds per Frame #!EF 
text field, changing it to the minimum number of seconds you 
want any given frame to be displayed. #!N #!I30 #!N 3. 
Click on the  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   Close #!EF button. The new rate takes 
effect. #!N #!I0 #!N #!EF #!N You can also set the 
throttle value by using the  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   throttle #!EF parameter to the 
Image tool (see Image in IBM Visualization Data Explorer User's Reference). 
